{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node3D\/globalRotation"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Rotation part of the global transformation in radians, specified in terms of YXZ-Euler angles in the format (X angle, Y angle, Z angle)."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node3d\/globalrotation"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"globalRotation","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Vector3","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector3","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector3V"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the mathematical sense, rotation is a matrix and not a vector. The three Euler angles, which are the three independent parameters of the Euler-angle parametrization of the rotation matrix, are stored in a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector3","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" data structure not because the rotation is a vector, but only because "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector3"},{"type":"text","text":" exists as a convenient data-structure to store 3 floating-point numbers. Therefore, applying affine operations on the rotation “vector” is not meaningful."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note","typ